    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** serving as our primary offensive anchors. **Gunnar Henderson** stands as our highest-rated option at 73.38, bolstered by a 16% park factor uplift and a favorable matchup against Lambert; his placement in the leadoff spot maximizes his opportunity to contribute across our categories. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a strong play at 67.95, as he benefits from a generous 4.51 xERA projection from the opposing starter, Ober. While **Jacob Wilson** (67.51) is technically subject to lineup confirmation, his projected placement in the #5 hole combined with a significant 10% park boost makes him a high-upside play for those seeking a balance of efficiency and volume.\n\nWe are navigating a tight margin with **Coby Mayo**, who landed just below our \"Zebras\" floor at 39.99. While **Coby Mayo** benefits from the same park-driven upside as **Gunnar Henderson**, his projected #8 spot in the order significantly depressed his potential, ultimately keeping him on the bench. Conversely, we are keeping a close watch on **Nasim Nunez** (45.93); while his base score is modest, he remains active due to our strategic emphasis on stolen bases. Despite the presence of a tough arm in Peralta, the fact that Peralta allows a 92% SB rate gives **Nasim Nunez** a distinct situational edge that mere raw production numbers might overlook. \n\nRisks for the day center on the uncertainty of the daily lineups, as we are currently operating with assumed positions for both **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jacob Wilson**. Additionally, **Heliot Ramos** faces a challenging matchup against a sub-3.00 xERA starter in S\u00e1nchez. While his score of 46.99 is sufficient to merit a start, we are monitoring the early game environment closely. On the injury front, the absence of **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Kyle Tucker** continues to limit our ceiling, but the depth of our bench\u2014including **Andy Pages**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Josh Jung**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Brady House**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Liam Hicks**\u2014ensures we maintain roster flexibility throughout this busy stretch of the season.",
